IN THE NEWS




Researchers Develop an App That Detects Mpox Rashes Using Artificial Intelligence
The free, open-source PoxApp recognizes skin lesions caused by mpox, formerly known as monkeypox, with 90% accuracy in less than five minutes.
Read more »



























































IN THE NEWS




Single Drug Injection Wards Off COVID-19 Hospitalizations
In a Stanford Medicine-led trial of nearly 2,000 COVID-19 patients, an injection of a biological drug given within seven days of symptom onset cut the likelihood of hospitalization in half.
Read more »



























































IN THE NEWS




Stanford Medicine Gave Over $950 Million to Our Community
In 2022, Stanford Health Care, Stanford Health Care Tri-Valley, and Stanford Medicine Children’s Health donated funds and services to improve access to health care, housing, and nutrition.
